      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<div class=\"contentLayout2\">\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<p>In Katana, you can specify the surface orientation (normal direction) of objects using the PrmanObjectStatements node.</p><p>The handedness of a coordinate system is referred to as its orientation. The initial &quot;camera&quot; coordinate system is left-handed: x points right, y point up, and z points in. Transformations, however, can flip the orientation of the current coordinate system. An example of a transformation that does not preserve orientation is a reflection.</p><p>Similarly, geometric primitives have an orientation, which determines whether their surface normals are defined using a right-handed or left-handed rule in their object coordinate system. RfK assume right-handed orientation: x points right, y point up, and z points out. <span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Positive rotation is </span>counterclockwise. If a primitive is inside-out, its normal will be computed so that it points in the opposite direction. This has implications for culling, shading, and solids (nested dielectrics for example). The outside surface of a primitive is the side from which the normal points outward; the inside surface is the opposite side. The interior of a solid is the volume that is adjacent to the inside surface and the exterior is the region adjacent to the outside.</p><p>If the current orientation is not the same as the orientation of the current coordinate system, geometric primitives are turned inside out, and their normals are automatically flipped.</p><p><br/></p><p>Below the teapot create macro is rendered with sides = 1, meaning only single sided. Black teapots indicates the object normals are inward facing, by default PxrSurface does not shade the inside of non-transmissive objects.</p></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout two-equal\" data-layout=\"two-equal\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"insideOrient.png\" width=\"512\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546178221/insideOrient.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531529602&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=512&amp;height=512\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/546178221/insideOrient.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531529602&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"512\" data-width=\"512\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"546178236\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"insideOrient.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"546178221\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"6332313a-aaf5-486d-96a2-bde8091171d0\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546178221/insideOrient.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531529602&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=512&amp;height=512 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546178221/insideOrient.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531529602&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=512&amp;height=512 1x\"></span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"reverseOrient.png\" width=\"512\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546178221/reverseOrient.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531529602&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=512&amp;height=512\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/546178221/reverseOrient.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531529602&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"512\" data-width=\"512\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"546178233\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"reverseOrient.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"546178221\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"fab280b9-d061-4b6e-9945-48f2a2391de0\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546178221/reverseOrient.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531529602&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=512&amp;height=512 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546178221/reverseOrient.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531529602&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=512&amp;height=512 1x\"></span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<ul><li><p>Reverse - Reverses from whatever the current coordinate system is regardless of its selection.</p></li></ul><p>Sides options:</p><ul><li><p>2 - default, means both sides are renderable/visible</p></li><li><p>1 - only the outward normal facing side is rendered/visible. Useful for backface culling visibility tricks.</p></li></ul></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>"
    }
